EmailTemplate.subject: Invitation from the Registrar: An evening with Dr Collier - How Education Works, Wednesday 8 June
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Lead.FirstName}
I’m delighted to invite you to join our parent community for a talk by our Head of School, Dr Collier covering many topics relevant to modern schooling, including how schooling is changing (refer topic list below). The also includes a Q&A session with Dr Collier.
Wednesday 8 June, 6.30pm
Heath Centre, Level 5, St Andrew’s Cathedral School
Bookings essential. Please reserve your place at www.trybooking.com/KUBF.
Regards Bruce Perry
Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
Need answers to the following? Please join us on Wednesday June 8 at 6.30pm for an evening with Dr John Collier.
How is education changing? What can we expect for our children in terms of teaching and assessment styles? What is the flipped classroom, Project Based Learning, Visible Learning and how do they impact on my child? As societal trends show more students at risk in terms of depression, anxiety and self-harm, what programs is the school offering to develop emotional wholeness in young people? How is the school responding to current educational issues such as STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics), Coding, Creativity and Design Innovation? Is student intelligence (IQ) a fixed commodity, or can it develop? With the advent of the International Baccalaureate Middle Years Program and growing numbers in the IB Diploma program, is the school actively pushing students towards the IB? How does the relationship between the HSC and university entry actually work?
What is the effect of the school’s Band 6 results in the HSC? Are schools scaled in a way which affects students? Universities appear to be moving away from sole reliance on the ATAR (Australian Tertiary Admissions Rank). What is happening? Are there other ways to get into university? Are there particular subjects students should choose, to maximise university entry opportunities? What is the importance of NAPLAN, PISA and TIMMS results? How does school funding work? Are schools going to become more expensive? What does the research evidence say about coeducational schools versus single sex schools? In terms of administration of SACS, what is the relationship between the Senior Executive, the School Council, Parents & Friends Association (P&F), the Foundation, the Cathedral and the Anglican Church? Who controls Education – the Federal Government through its Department of Education, the State Government or individual schools?
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
St Andrew's Cathedral School
Sydney Square, Sydney NSW 2000, Australia direct +61 2 9286 9507 mobile 0418 255 923 email BPerry@sacs.nsw.edu.au phone +61 2 9286 9500 fax +61 29286 9550
